PART 7 — Add Jenkinsfile / Pipeline Script

Your notes contain incomplete pipeline syntax.

Here is the corrected version.

Pipeline Script

Paste inside Pipeline Script section:

pipeline {
    agent any

    tools {
        maven 'Maven3'
    }

    stages {

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean install'
            }
        }

        stage('SonarQube Analysis') {
            steps {
                withSonarQubeEnv('My SonarQube Server') {
                    sh 'mvn sonar:sonar'
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
IMPORTANT FOR WINDOWS

If Jenkins runs on Windows directly:

Replace:

sh

with:

bat

So:

bat 'mvn clean install'

and:

bat 'mvn sonar:sonar'
What This Pipeline Does
Stage 1 — Build
mvn clean install

Builds Maven project.

Stage 2 — SonarQube Analysis
mvn sonar:sonar

Runs code quality analysis.

